<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/173: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-08T10:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">July 8,
                                        1922—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:30
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. Has Department approved terms of loan contract as finally signed by
                            Keith and Keilhauer on June 24th and received here yesterday? It is to
                            be presented to the Congress on Monday for approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>